      "comment": "ZIPPING KLIMENKO (3) is a talented type and proved too classy last time to win by 0.8 lengths at Gosford in a handy 22.77 beating Tatooine. Safe beginner who has drawn to advantage. Well placed and can measure up. VINTAGE RACER (4) showed little early speed at his last couple, the latest finishing fourth (23.49) in a Grade 5 at this track. Must be included in calculations. ROOKIE RED (1) turned in a plain performance last time when sixth at this track over 272m behind Miss Arizona (16.49) in a Grade 4/5. Consistent performer from this draw with a win and four minor placings to his credit. Has ability and can measure up. HOOKED ON HOPE (8) cannot be left out after placing here at this trip last start.",
